# shell/zinit-uninstall.list — zinit plugins this fork used to load
# but no longer does. Read every run by install.sh; each entry is an
# `owner/repo` spec (the same form passed to `zinit light`).
#
# To activate: rename this file to `shell/zinit-uninstall.list` (drop the
# `.example` suffix) and add one plugin spec per line.
#
# Why this exists: removing a `zinit light X` line from your zshrc.local
# stops loading the plugin into the next zsh session, but does NOT clean
# up zinit's plugin cache at ~/.local/share/zinit/plugins/<owner>---<repo>/.
# Listing the spec here makes install.sh do `rm -rf` on the cache the next
# time it runs (idempotent — silent when already absent).
#
# Format: one `owner/repo` per line. Comments (#) and blank lines ignored.
# Sandbox: entries containing `..` or starting/ending with `/` are rejected.
#
# Workflow when retiring a zinit plugin:
#   1. Remove the `zinit light owner/repo` line from shell/zshrc.local
#   2. Add `owner/repo` here (in this same commit)
#   3. Run `bash install.sh` — install.sh purges the cache.
#
# Without step 2, the plugin keeps loading from cache forever on machines
# that already had it installed.

# Examples (uncomment to use):
#
# MichaelAquilina/zsh-you-should-use
# old-org/abandoned-plugin
